On August 14, Ukrainian UAVs from the Special Operations Forces of the AFU attacked the Olya Port (Astrakhan Oblast) in the Caspian Sea.
As a result, the vessel "Port Olya 4" was hit and is now sinking. The Ukrainian General Staff claimed that it held components for Geran-2/3 drones as well as ammunition from Iran.

On August 14, Ukrainian UAVs from the Special Operations Forces of the AFU attacked the Olya Port (Astrakhan Oblast) in the Caspian Sea.
As a result, the vessel "Port Olya 4" was hit and is now sinking. The Ukrainian General Staff claimed that it held components for Geran-2/3 drones as well as ammunition from Iran.
An explosion was heard from Sumy City. This was a ground-to-ground type S-300 missile.

Footage showing today's training of a Tu-95MS strategic bomber from Engels-2 Airbase, Saratov Oblast.
Interestingly, the bomber is not equipped with Kh-101 cruise missiles, confirming that not all bombers at the airbase have been equipped. Recently, Tu-95s have been flying to and from Ukrainka Airbase, Amur Oblast to be equipped with missiles.

My prediction for today's peace talks:
Putin puts forth his baseline demands for a long-term ceasefire in Ukraine.
Trump refuses because it's in America's best interests to keep Ukrainians fighting Russians. 
Putin flies back to Moscow and Trump flies back to Washington.
Trump is silent for a day or two and then makes a post on Truth Social (similar to his one a couple months ago with the missile attack), expressing his "disappointment" in Putin for not ending the war, but using the fact that he even tried to negotiate with Putin to further promote himself as the "president of peace". 
Zelensky makes an address using these failed talks to continue claiming that Putin doesn't want peace, while indirectly and subtly mocking Trump for even trying to negotiate with terrorists.
Medvedev makes a few harsh tweets about the U.S. and Ukraine. 
The war continues, and hundreds of thousands of more Russians and Ukrainians die over the next 2-ish years.
